      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i tried the log transform but the tails are still pretty beefy. i'm seeing some really extreme outliers that are pulling the line way off. are there other ways to deal with these extreme deviations without just deleting rows? maybe something like robust regression or switching to a different error distribution?",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "thanks. i tried the log transform but the tails are still pretty beefy. i'm seeing some really extreme outliers that are pulling the line way off. are there other ways to deal with these extreme deviations without just deleting rows? maybe something like robust regression or switching to a different error distribution?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
